
  <sn><md>#### Lessivage

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-9
The `mechanical migration` of small mineral particles `from the A to the B horizons` of a soil, producing in B horizons relative enrichment in clay (argillic horizons).
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-3
![img](https://cdn8.futura-sciences.com/sources/images/glossaire/lessivage-sol-schema_arpent-nourricier-CC-by-sa.jpg)
:::
:::

* `Depletion of clay` in ++A horizon++.
* `Enrichment of clay content in B` horizon in comparison to C and/or A horizon.
* `Presence of argillans` in the B horizon and C-horizon.
* `Higher fine clay/total clay ratio` in the B horizon than in the A horizon.

The ++mobile clay++ involved may be a `product of weathering in the A horizon` or added to the soil during development.
</md></sn>
