<sn><md>#### Pedoturbation

Biological, physical (freeze-thaw and wet-dry cycles) `churning and cycling of soil materials`, thereby homogenizing the solum in varying degrees
Pedoturbation is the process of `mixing in the soil`. A `certain amount of mixing` is `always taking place` in the soils. `Seven kinds of pedoturbations` are recognised:


**Kinds of Pedoturbation**

| Kind of Pedoturbation | Definition / Description | Key Examples &amp; Context |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Faunal** | Soil mixing by `animals` | Ants, earthworms, moles, rodents, and man himself |
| **Floral** | Mixing by `plants` | Tree tipping that forms pits and mounds |
| **Congelli** | Mixing by `freeze-thaw cycles` | Found in tundra and alpine landscapes |
| **Argilli** | Mixing of material in the solum by `mass-wasting movements` of expansible clays or churning processes caused by swell-shrink clays | Observed in deep black cotton soils of Maharashtra, Madhya Pradesh, Gujarat, etc. |
| **Crystal** | Mixing by `growth of crystals` | Halite ($\text{NaCl}$) crystal growth |
| **Aqua** | Mixing by `upwelling currents of water` | Takes place within the solum |
| **Seismo** | Mixing by `vibration` | Earthquake tremors |</md></sn>